  "prompt": "Which is the best Android app locker?",
  "response": "Choosing the \"best\" Android app locker can depend on your specific needs and preferences, but several popular options are often recommended based on features, user reviews, and security:\n\n1. **AppLock** by DoMobile Lab:\n   - User-friendly interface.\n   - Supports locking apps, photos, and videos.\n   - Offers features like a fake cover, intruder selfie, and password recovery options.\n\n2. **Norton App Lock**:\n   - Developed by Norton, a trusted name in security.\n   - Allows you to lock individual apps and maintain privacy.\n   - Simple to use with a no-frills interface.\n\n3. **Smart AppLock**:\n   - Provides robust locking features and supports a wide array of apps.\n   - Offers various security options, including PIN, pattern, and fingerprint.\n   - Multi-language support and customizable settings.\n\n4. **AppLock Pro**:\n   - Focuses on strong security features.\n   - Offers customizable themes and options for hidden apps.\n   - Includes a vault for safeguarding private files.\n\n5. **Hexlock**:\n   - Unique feature of creating profiles for different situations (e.g., work, home).\n   - Allows for locking apps based on context.\n   - Simple and clean interface.\n\n6. **Zarden**:\n   - Known for its lightweight design.\n   - Offers robust security options and a user-friendly experience.\n\nBefore choosing an app locker, consider factors like the level of security you need, features that matter to you (such as intruder alerts, customization options, or ease of use), and whether you prefer a free app or are willing to pay for premium features. Always check for the latest reviews and updates, as app performance can change with new updates.",
